Replay of BUET CSE Freshers' Reception Programming Contest 2023

B - A Tale of Two Jarins

Time Limit
1 seconds
Memory Limit
128 MB

    You're familiar with multiplication tables right?

    In case your aren't, here's an intro. Multiplication table means a 2-dimensional array with $n$ rows and $m$ columns where all possible products between two numbers in this range are displayed.

    Here goes a picture for a multiplcation table with $8$ rows and $12$ columns.

    The beauty of a multiplication table equals to the product of all the numbers written on it. For instance, the beauty of a $3 \times 2$ table($3$ rows, $2$ columns) equals $288$.

    Now the most famous duo of the Jarinverse named "Jarin Tasneem" and "Jarin Tasnim" (getting confused huh? hold on...) decide to a play an exciting game. Each of them contructs a multiplication table of her own and calculates the beauty of the table. The player whose table turns out to be more beautiful, wins the match. However, if the beauty of the tables are exactly the same, the match ends in a draw.

    If the match ends in a draw, print Draw. Otherwise print the name of the winner Jarin Tasneem or Jarin Tasnim.

    Input

    Input starts with an integer T ($\leq 1000$), denoting the number of test cases.

    Each case consists of a line containing four integers $n1, m1, n2, m2$ ($1\leq n1, m1, n2, m2 \leq 1000$) denoting the number of rows and columns for Jarin Tasneem and Jarin Tasnim for that match respectively.

    Output

    For each case, if the game ends in a conclusion, print the name of the winner "Jarin Tasneem" or "Jarin Tasnim".(without quotes) In case of a tie, print "Draw".(without quotes)

    Sample

    Input Output
    Click to copy

    5 2 3 1 4 1 2 3 4 1 4 4 1 5 6 4 7 3 3 5 2

    Click to copy

    Jarin Tasneem Jarin Tasnim Draw Jarin Tasneem Jarin Tasnim
